ith a small parish in upstate New York, and Schrader seizes on the austerity of his world: The film is quiet and contemplative, which makes its apocalyptic, shattering conclusion all the more impactful. (Also recommended: the small but powerful indie dramas “<b>The Messenger</b>” and “<b>We Need to Talk About Kevin</b>.”)</p></div><div class="WhereToWatchInline__whereToWatchSimple ListRecUnit__whereToWatch" data-reactid="162"><div class="WhereToWatchInline__rundownLoading" data-reactid="163"><span data-reactid="164"></span><span style="font-size:0;" data-reactid="165"></span></div></div><hr class="ListRecUnit__listRecommendationHorizontalRule" data-reactid="166"/></div></div><div class="ListV2__ad row" data-reactid="167"><!-- react-empty: 168 --></div><div class="ListRecUnit__listRecommendationItem" data-reactid="169"><div class="full-bleed-image-mobile" data-reactid="170"><a class="ListRecUnit__postImageLink" href="https://www.nytimes.com/watching/titles/willy-wonka-and-the-chocolate-factory" data-reactid="171"><div data-reactid="172"><div class="CreditedMedia__watchedBadgeCreditedMediaContainer" data-reactid="173"><!-- react-empty: 174 --><picture data-reactid="175"><img src="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2018/11/28/arts/28dahlnetflix-item/merlin_136157250_6089758a-7a3f-4196-a33e-7758a147a267-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" class="CreditedMedia__img" data-reactid="176"/></picture></div><div class="CreditedMedia__creditAndCaption" data-reactid="177"><span class="CreditedMedia__caption" data-reactid="178">Gene Wilder in “Willy Wonka and the Chocolate Factory,” adapted from Roald Dahl’s “Charlie and the Chocolate Factory.”</span><span class="CreditedMedia__credit" data-reactid="179">Paramount Pictures</span></div></div></a></div><div class="ListRecUnit__listRecommendationCopy" data-reactid="180"><p class="ListRecUnit__typeHeader" data-reactid="181">Movie</p><h2 data-reactid="182"><a class="ListRecUnit__recTitle shouldStayInPage" href="https://www.nytimes.com/watching/titles/willy-wonka-and-the-chocolate-factory" data-reactid="183"><span class="ListRecUnit__recTitleText" data-reactid="184">‘Willy Wonka and the Chocolate Factory’</span></a></h2><div class="WatchingLink__watchingLink stayInPage" data-reactid="185"><button class="SaveToWatchlistButton__saveToWatchlistButton stayInPage" data-reactid="186"><div class="_sharedIconStyles__SVGiconContainer" data-reactid="187"><svg width="15px" height="21px" viewBox="0 0 15 21" version="1.1" data-reactid="188"><title data-reactid="189">Save To Watch</title><desc data-reactid="190">Ribbon</desc><g id="RibbonIcon" stroke="none" stroke-width="1" fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd" data-reactid="191"><g class="SaveToWatchlistButton__inactiveIcon" id="bookmark" transform="translate(1.000000, 1.000000)" stroke-width="2" stroke="#000000" data-reactid="192"><polygon id="ribbon" points="0 0 0 18.1314829 6.5 13.7981496 13 18.1314829 13 0" data-reactid="193"></polygon></g></g></svg></div><span class="SaveToWatchlistButton__buttonText" data-reactid="194">Save to Watch</span></button><button class="LikeButton__likeButton" data-reactid="195"><div class="_sharedIconStyles__SVGiconContainer" data-reactid="196"><svg width="24px" height="21px" viewBox="0 0 24 21" version="1.1" data-reactid="197"><title data-reactid="198">Like</title><desc data-reactid="199">Heart Shape</desc><g id="Like" stroke="none" stroke-width="1" fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd" data-reactid="200"><g class="LikeButton__inactiveIcon" id="heart" transform="translate(1.000000, 1.000000)" stroke="#000000" stroke-width="2" data-reactid="201"><path d="M20.4997045,9.1706201 C21.4801158,8.1903106 22,6.86489899 22,5.37571157 C22,3.9415837 21.4377553,2.59810513 20.4193068,1.5801398 C19.4007673,0.56208345 18.0563988,0 16.6212625,0 C15.1861261,0 13.8417576,0.56208345 12.8232181,1.5801398 L11,3.40249296 L9.1767819,1.5801398 C8.1582424,0.56208345 6.81387391,0 5.37873754,0 C3.94360117,0 2.59923268,0.56208345 1.58069315,1.5801398 C0.56224468,2.59810513 0,3.9415837 0,5.37571157 C0,6.80983945 0.56224468,8.153318 1.57930226,9.1698958 L11.0398671,18.5888901 L20.4997045,9.1706201 Z" id="Shape" data-reactid="202"></path></g></g></svg></div><span class="LikeButton__buttonText" data-reactid="203">Like</span></button></div><div class="ListRecUnit__description" data-reactid="204"><p data-reactid="205">Gene Wilder created one of cinema’s most enduring characters in this 1971 adaptation of Roald Dahl’s classic novel “Charlie and the Chocolate Factory,” directed by Mel Stuart. As the gloriously eccentric owner of the best candy factory in all the land, Wilder invests the character with not only a sense of wonder and imagination but also a surprising edginess — this is ultimately a morality tale, in which a guided tour of the factory becomes a lesson in the consequences of childish behavior. Innovative and filled with memorable songs and supporting characters, this is a family film with a welcome dash of darkness. (For more family-friendly comedy, queue up “<b>Galaxy Quest</b>.”)</p></div><div class="WhereToWatchInline__whereToWatchSimple ListRecUnit__whereToWatch" data-reactid="206"><div class="WhereToWatchInline__rundownLoading" data-reactid="207"><span data-reactid="208"></span><span style="font-size:0;" data-reactid="209"></span></div></div><hr class="ListRecUnit__listRecommendationHorizontalRule" data-reactid="210"/></div></div><div class="ListRecUnit__listRecommendationItem" data-reactid="211"><div class="full-bleed-image-mobile" data-reactid="212"><a class="ListRecUnit__postImageLink" href="https://www.nytimes.com/watching/titles/brazil-watching" data-reactid="213"><div data-reactid="214"><div class="CreditedMedia__watchedBadgeCreditedMediaContainer" data-reactid="215"><!-- react-empty: 216 --><picture data-reactid="217"><img src="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2019/01/25/arts/25BRAZIL/25BRAZIL-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" class="CreditedMedia__img" data-reactid="218"/></picture></div><div class="CreditedMedia__cr