ing through upstate New York before ultimately revealing a chilling connection. The performances are sharp and the scares are genuine, while Perkins’ orchestration of mood and atmosphere is chillingly effective. (Also recommended: the 1990 psychological thriller “<b>Jacob’s Ladder</b>.”)</p></div><div class="WhereToWatchInline__whereToWatchSimple ListRecUnit__whereToWatch" data-reactid="2280"><div class="WhereToWatchInline__rundownLoading" data-reactid="2281"><span data-reactid="2282"></span><span style="font-size:0;" data-reactid="2283"></span></div></div><hr class="ListRecUnit__listRecommendationHorizontalRule" data-reactid="2284"/></div></div></div></div><div data-reactid="2285"></div></div><hr class="full-bleed-border" data-reactid="2286"/><div class="container" data-reactid="2287"><div class="GWIAttribution__gwiLink" data-reactid="2288"><!-- react-text: 2289 -->Streaming information by<!-- /react-text --><a href="https://gowatchit.com" target="_blank" data-reactid="2290">GoWatchIt</a></div></div></div></main><footer class="Footer__footer" data-reactid="2291"><div class="container" data-reactid="2292"><div class="row" data-reactid="2293"><div class="col-sm-6" data-reactid="2294"><section class="Footer__footerBlock" data-reactid="2295"><h4 class="Footer__promptTile" data-reactid="2296">Have questions? Feedback?</h4><div class="Footer__promptSubtitle" data-reactid="2297"><p data-reactid="2298"><!-- react-text: 2299 -->Read our <!-- /react-text --><a href="//www.nytimes.com/2017/01/10/watching/faq.html" title="faq" data-reactid="2300">FAQs</a><!-- react-text: 2301 --> or <!-- /react-text --><a href="mailto:watchingcare@nytimes.com" target="_blank" data-reactid="2302">contact us</a><!-- react-text: 2303 --> to let us know how we’re doing.<!-- /react-text --></p></div></section></div><div class="col-sm-6" data-reactid="2304"><section class="Footer__footerBlock" data-reactid="2305"><h4 class="Footer__promptTile" data-reactid="2306">Let’s be friends.</h4><div class="Fo