l while an impatient world and trigger-happy military clamor for answers and bend to paranoia. “Arrival” delivers the expected doses of excitement and awe, but this is primarily a film of ideas. It challenges how we think about not only these kinds of stories but also the world at large. (For more action-oriented sci-fi, try Paul Verhoeven’s “<b>Total Recall</b>.”)","imageCrops":{"thumbnail":{"height":252,"width":252,"url":"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2017/01/23/watching/arrival-watching/arrival-watching-smallSquare252.jpg"},"largeImage":{"height":900,"width":1600,"url":"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2017/01/23/watching/arrival-watching/arrival-watching-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg"},"smallImage":{"height":293,"width":440,"url":"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2017/01/23/watching/arrival-watching/arrival-watching-mediumThreeByTwo440.jpg"},"facebook":{"height":550,"width":1050,"url":"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2017/01/23/watching/arrival-watching/arrival-watching-facebookJumbo.jpg"},"recCard":{"height":432,"width":768,"url":"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2017/01/23/watching/arrival-watching/arrival-watching-videoSixteenByNine768.jpg"},"recCardSmallScreens":{"height":322,"width":573,"url":"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2017/01/23/watching/arrival-watching/arrival-watching-largeWidescreen573.jpg"},"largeHorizontal":{"height":683,"width":1024,"url":"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2017/01/23/watching/arrival-watching/arrival-watching-largeHorizontalJumbo.jpg"},"master":{"height":512,"width":768,"url":"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2017/01/23/watching/arrival-watching/arrival-watching-master768.jpg"},"master1050":{"height":700,"width":1050,"url":"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2017/01/23/watching/arrival-watching/arrival-watching-master1050.jpg"},"superJumbo":{"height":1366,"width":2048,"url":"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2017/01/23/watching/arrival-watching/arrival-watching-superJumbo.jpg"}},"imageCredit":"Jan Thijs/Paramount Pictures","watchIfTe