aises the child as his own and must then summon all his ingenuity to keep their makeshift family intact. Even this first time out, Chaplin juggles the seemingly incongruent tones with ease. The comic beats are uproarious, but the scenes of separation and reunion are gut-wrenching, thanks in no small part to the heartbreaking performance of little Jackie Coogan in the title role. (Silent movie fanatics will also want to stream the Amazon original “<b>Wonderstruck</b>.”)","imageCrops":{"thumbnail":{"height":252,"width":252,"url":"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2014/08/14/watching/the-kid-watching/the-kid-watching-smallSquare252.jpg"},"largeImage":{"height":900,"width":1599,"url":"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2014/08/14/watching/the-kid-watching/the-kid-watching-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg"},"smallImage":{"height":293,"width":440,"url":"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2014/08/14/watching/the-kid-watching/the-kid-watching-mediumThreeByTwo440.jpg"},"facebook":{"height":550,"width":1050,"url":"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2014/08/14/watching/the-kid-watching/the-kid-watching-facebookJumbo.jpg"},"recCard":{"height":432,"width":768,"url":"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2014/08/14/watching/the-kid-watching/the-kid-watching-videoSixteenByNine768.jpg"},"recCardSmallScreens":{"height":322,"width":573,"url":"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2014/08/14/watching/the-kid-watching/the-kid-watching-largeWidescreen573.jpg"},"largeHorizontal":{"height":683,"width":1024,"url":"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2014/08/14/watching/the-kid-watching/the-kid-watching-largeHorizontalJumbo.jpg"},"master":{"height":471,"width":768,"url":"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2014/08/14/watching/the-kid-watching/the-kid-watching-master768.jpg"},"master1050":{"height":644,"width":1050,"url":"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2014/08/14/watching/the-kid-watching/the-kid-watching-master1050.jpg"},"superJumbo":{"height":980,"width":1599,"url":"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2014/08/14/watching/th